Key Career Highlights
Four-Time World Champion: Won consecutive titles in 2010, 2011, 2012, and 2013.
Youngest Champion: Became the youngest-ever Formula One World Champion.
Career Wins: 53 Grand Prix victories (ranks high on the all-time list).
Teams: Competed for BMW Sauber, Toro Rosso, Red Bull Racing, Ferrari, and Aston Martin.
Record Setter: Set records for the most consecutive wins (9), most wins in a season (13, in 2013), and most pole positions in a season (15, in 2011).
Final F1 Season: Retired after the 2022 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix after two years with Aston Martin. 
